Background

		Dr. Jeffrey W. Runge, M.D. serves as a Principal at The Chertoff Group. Dr. Runge is the Founder of Biologue, Inc. and serves as its President. From 2001 to August 2008, Dr. Runge served in the Bush administration, first as the head of the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration, confirmed by the Senate in August 2001. In September 2005, he became the Department of Homeland Security's first Chief Medical Officer and founded the DHS Office of Health Affairs in ... 2007. He was confirmed by the Senate as DHS' first Assistant Secretary for Health Affairs in December of 2007. Dr. Runge served as Acting DHS Undersecretary for Science and Technology from February 2006 to August 2006. In his role at DHS, Dr. Runge oversaw the operations of the department's biodefense activities, medical preparedness and workforce health protection, including managing DHS' role in Project BioShield, working with the various federal departments on medical countermeasure assurance. Prior to joining DHS, Dr. Runge served as Assistant Chairman of the Department of Emergency Medicine at the Carolinas Medical Center in Charlotte, NC, from 1984 to 2001. Dr. Runge has been Director of Conmed Healthcare Management, Inc. since January 18, 2011. Dr. Runge has been an Independent Director of PharmAthene, Inc. since December 21, 2009. Dr. Runge earned his medical degree from the Medical University of South Carolina and his undergraduate degree from the University of the South.Read Full Background




